<LegalLayout
  title="Privacy · Intervene"
  description="Privacy policy for the Intervene Limited website."
  heading="Privacy policy."
  updated="March 2026"
  current="legal"
>
  <h2>1. Who we are</h2>
  <p>
    Intervene Limited is an independent advisory practice based in the
    United Kingdom. For the purposes of UK GDPR, Intervene Limited is the
    data controller for any personal data submitted via this site or in the
    course of a confidential enquiry.
  </p>

  <h2>2. What we collect</h2>
  <p>Through the contact form, we collect:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Name</li>
    <li>Organisation</li>
    <li>Email address</li>
    <li>Role (optional)</li>
    <li>The free-text description of the situation prompting the enquiry</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    This site uses no analytics cookies, no tracking pixels, and no
    advertising trackers. We do not profile visitors. We do not use
    third-party scripts beyond the Google Fonts CDN, which serves typeface
    files.
  </p>

  <h2>3. How we use it</h2>
  <p>
    Personal data is used solely to respond to the enquiry and to determine
    whether an engagement is appropriate. It is not used for marketing, not
    shared with third parties, and not retained beyond what is necessary to
    handle the enquiry or to comply with the engagement-related
    record-keeping obligations of an active or recently concluded contract.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Third-party processors</h2>
  <p>
    The contact form is transmitted via Formspree (Formspree, Inc.), which
    acts solely as the transmission mechanism. Formspree's processing is
    governed by its own data processing terms. No other third-party
    processor receives form submissions.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Your rights</h2>
  <p>
    Under UK GDPR you have the right to access, correct, or request deletion
    of personal data we hold about you. To exercise these rights, use the
    <a href="/Intervene/contact/">contact form</a>. We respond to such requests within
    one calendar month.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Governing law</h2>
  <p>
    This policy is governed by UK GDPR and the Data Protection Act 2018. The
    supervisory authority for England and Wales is the Information
    Commissioner's Office
    (<a href="https://ico.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ico.org.uk</a>).
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
